From zarrar.shehzad at yale.edu  Wed Sep 21 07:09:39 2011
From: zarrar.shehzad at yale.edu (Zarrar Shehzad)
Date: Wed, 21 Sep 2011 01:09:39 -0400
Subject: [Rcpp-devel] Easy way to subset a matrix
In-Reply-To: <002A598E-1B41-4C0C-BB09-02BF4F7039D8@ucla.edu>
References: <002A598E-1B41-4C0C-BB09-02BF4F7039D8@ucla.edu>
Message-ID: <CAP5OcM9cVFkiDT5BndfFfiKU8tH4oZjhWLjQ6iRYoBp=mFgmAA@mail.gmail.com>

I am not sure if there are native functions in Rcpp but you could use
RcppArmadillo to solve your problem.

So say Xs = x:

// Convert from SEXP => Rcpp => Arma
Rcpp::NumericMatrix Xr(Xs);
arma::mat X(Xr.begin(), Xr.nrow(), Xr.ncol(), false);

// Get subset of matrix and calculate variance
// (i.e., do var(x[3:10,5]))
arma::var( X.submat(3, 10, 5, 5) );

The armadillo docs are really nice so you can see those for more info on the
var and submat functions.

Cheers
Zarrar

