From darren at dcook.org  Thu Sep 22 12:06:12 2011
From: darren at dcook.org (Darren Cook)
Date: Thu, 22 Sep 2011 19:06:12 +0900
Subject: [Rcpp-devel] is std::sort function broken??
In-Reply-To: <D6316AEF-B651-4CF6-BDAD-82C0CCCE835C@ucla.edu>
References: <D6316AEF-B651-4CF6-BDAD-82C0CCCE835C@ucla.edu>
Message-ID: <4E7B0894.50204@dcook.org>

> 		std::sort(data.front(), data.back());

front() and back() return references to the first and last items. I.e.
they return doubles, not iterators. I think what you wanted was:
  std::sort(data.begin(),data.end());

Darren


